                        <i class="far fa-eye"></i>
                        <span>119 <span x-text="t[lang].reads">阅读</span></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </header>

            <!-- Featured Image -->
            <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-12 shadow-2xl shadow-slate-200/50">
                <img src="https://picsum.photos/seed/yiyu-20260518-creative/800/500" alt="Featured Image" class="w-full h-[400px] object-cover">
            </div>

            <!-- Rich Text Body -->
            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'zh'">
                <h2>CTR 是入口，不是结论</h2>
<p>素材复盘时，很多团队会把 CTR 当成最高指标。CTR 确实能说明开头和卖点是否吸引人，但它不能证明素材能带来有效客户。有些视频特别会制造好奇，却把不合适的人也吸引进来，最终咨询质量很低。</p>
<h2>把素材分成四类</h2>
<p>第一类是“能吸引但不能卖”，表现为 CTR 高、转化低。第二类是“能卖但量小”，点击一般，但咨询质量好。第三类是“能跑又能卖”，值得扩展同方向脚本。第四类是“无效素材”，曝光、点击、转化都弱，尽快停止。</p>
<h2>复盘表怎么做</h2>
<p>每条素材记录五列：前三秒留存、CTR、落地页停留、有效咨询、成交或回款。B2B 服务还可以加一列“客户是否符合目标画像”。这样复盘时不会被单一指标带偏。</p>
<blockquote>
<p>素材不是为了赢得点击，而是为了找到正确客户。点击只是通往成交的一段路。</p>
</blockquote>
            </div>
            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>CTR Is an Entrance, Not a Conclusion</h2>
<p>CTR shows whether a hook attracts attention, but it does not prove the creative brings qualified customers. Some videos create curiosity but attract the wrong audience.</p>
<h2>Four Creative Types</h2>
<p>Some creatives attract but do not sell: high CTR, low conversion. Some sell but do not scale: average clicks, strong lead quality. Some both scale and sell. Others are simply weak and should stop.</p>
<h2>Build a Review Sheet</h2>
<p>Track five columns: three-second retention, CTR, landing page time, qualified inquiries, and sales or payment. For B2B services, add whether the lead matches the target profile. This keeps the team from overreacting to one metric.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Social Share (Mock) -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-slate-100 flex items-center justify-between">
